so here. I'm workin'.

02:28.114 --> 02:30.776
Lying in a crumpled heap in an airport
parking lot. How's that pay?

02:30.850 --> 02:34.411
Look, mybuddygot into some trouble with
some guys and needed someone to talk to 'em.

02:34.487 --> 02:37.012
- I said I'd do it for a grand.
- Some guys?

02:37.090 --> 02:39.251
- What guys?
- Guys. I don't know.

02:39.325 --> 02:41.657
Look, I'm just trying
to make a living.

02:41.728 --> 02:44.925
Besides, you have no business giving me crap, Bro.
You're driving around in my car.

02:44.998 --> 02:48.695
- Your car?
- Yeah, I busted ass for an entire
summerworkin' on this car.

02:48.768 --> 02:50.929
Mom had no right to give it toyou.

02:51.004 --> 02:52.904
She said that Dad
wanted me to have it.

02:52.972 --> 02:54.963
Oh, okay. Soyou bailed...

02:55.041 --> 02:58.306
and I take a double dose of Dad's crap
foryears, and you get the car.

02:58.378 --> 03:03.543
- Yeah, that's-- that's fair.
- Nate, is this yourway of asking
me to helpyou with this job?

03:03.616 --> 03:06.244
- Is that what this is?
- Likeyou read minds, Bro.

03:10.423 --> 03:12.653
We work on this together...

03:12.725 --> 03:15.421
you clean upyour act.

03:30.210 --> 03:33.407
Ifl don't help him with this job,
he's gonna get himselfkilled.

03:33.479 --> 03:36.004
Oh, and now he's decided
that the car is his.

03:36.082 --> 03:38.915
I've never seen you this
attached to anything, Michael.

03:38.985 --> 03:41.783
Ifmy dad left me this car,
itwas for a very good reason.

03:41.854 --> 03:45.312
He wasn't the sort of guywho would just
leave me this because he was feeling generous.

03:45.391 --> 03:48.451
I almost lost a finger putting in that air filter.
I don't think he did you any favors.

03:48.528 --> 03:51.463
Yeah, well, that was more
his style. Try it now.

03:51.531 --> 03:54.364
[ Engine Cranks ]

03:54.434 --> 03:56.800
Uh, check the ignition.

03:58.938 --> 04:01.372
[Michael Sighs ]

04:06.946 --> 04:09.540
- You knowyou've got a bug in there.
- A bug?

04:09.616 --> 04:12.107
Underthe dash.
Looks like Sam's work.

04:12.185 --> 04:15.882
- Fi, you don't know it's Sam.
- I know Sam's style.

04:15.955 --> 04:18.923
I thought you had an arrangement.
He tells the feds what you're up to...

04:18.992 --> 04:21.290
- tellsyou what the feds are up to.
- I'll handle it.

04:21.361 --> 04:24.819
No, no, no, no. I'd be happy
to take care of it.

04:24.897 --> 04:26.865
There's nothing like
a smashed kneecap...

04:26.933 --> 04:28.867
to remind Sam who his friends are.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.869
Don't say anything.
I know it's there.

04:30.937 --> 04:33.701
They'll only hearwhat I want them to hear.
It's better this way.

04:33.773 --> 04:38.073
Is that tradecraft, Michael,
orjust protecting your friend?

04:38.144 --> 04:42.478
It's both, Fi. I gotta get cleaned up.
Can you put this back together?

04:42.548 --> 04:44.539
- Don't do--
- Look, I'll-- I'll behave.

04:47.820 --> 04:49.412
Maybe.

04:53.493 --> 04:55.688
I-I worked
airport security for a year.

04:57.897 --> 05:01.492
Uh, log planes in and out,
deal with the cargo manifests.

05:01.567 --> 05:05.333
So there's this family.
Lebanese, I think. The Zamars.

05:05.405 --> 05:07.896
They're two brothers and a dad.

05:07.974 --> 05:11.137
They run some kind of
import-export business.

05:11.210 --> 05:14.611
So the thing is,
we became kind offriends.

05:14.681 --> 05:17.115
- They gave me some stuff.
- Stuff? What kind of stuff?

05:17.183 --> 05:20.744
Basketball tickets,
some nice tequila...

05:20.820 --> 05:22.811
Ioaned me money a few times.

05:22.889 --> 05:24.914
M-Mywife's pregnant.

05:24.991 --> 05:28.722
We're trying to get ready
for the baby. It's been hard.

05:28.795 --> 05:31.127
I get it. You needed the money.
Go on.

05:31.197 --> 05:33.631
Anyway, I-- I did 'em some favors.

05:33.700 --> 05:35.793
I'd change arrival times
on planes on the log.

05:35.868 --> 05:38.393
It's against the rules,
but it seemed like little stuff.

05:38.471 --> 05:40.405
Then last week...

05:40.473 --> 05:44.933
they told me theywanted me to leave a flight
off the log entirely, and that's serious.

05:45.011 --> 05:47.309
I-I-I didn't want to do it.

05:47.380 --> 05:51.817
And I remembered, you know, Nate told me that
you two had this kind ofbusiness helpin' people.

05:51.884 --> 05:55.615
Nate said we had a business together,
the two of us, like a team?

05:55.688 --> 06:00.523
Yeah. Yeah. He-- He said he was gonna
talk to the guys and get 'em off my back.

06:00.593 --> 06:03.289
- I saw how well that went.
- They came to my house.

06:03.363 --> 06:06.457
They threatened me,
threatened mywife.

06:06.532 --> 06:10.434
I-- I said I was gonna quit myjob.
They said theywere gonna hurt me ifl did.

06:10.503 --> 06:12.903
I just want to give the money back
and walk away.

06:12.972 --> 06:14.803
Can you just
talk to 'em and--

06:15.908 --> 06:17.899
It's a little late forthat,Jake.

06:20.012 --> 06:22.003
I know I screwed up, okay? I--

06:22.081 --> 06:24.311
I just don't want my family
to pay for it.

06:25.418 --> 06:27.852
And mywife-- She--

06:27.920 --> 06:31.515
I'm barelyhangin'on
to heras it is, man.

06:32.892 --> 06:34.826
I don't know what else to do.

06:34.894 --> 06:36.885
Please.

06:39.332 --> 06:41.596
- I'll look into it.
- Thanks.

06:46.038 --> 06:49.064
- I told your friend I'd help him out. You happy?
- You should be too.

06:49.142 --> 06:51.440
- I'm hustling you work.
- Yeah, it's almost like we're a team.

06:51.511 --> 06:55.641
- You want to get in the car?
- Hey, about the car, did Mom showyou Dad's will?

06:55.715 --> 06:58.149
No. All I saw was
an old pack of Kools...

06:58.217 --> 07:00.879
and an unfinished to-do list.

07:00.953 --> 07:03.046
Come on. You hated him.

07:03.122 --> 07:06.683
I put up with his crap.
I rebuilt the car's engine.

07:06.759 --> 07:09.023
[ Engine Cranks ]

07:11.697 --> 07:14.962
I'll giveyou the distributor cap
ifyou agreewe should find Dad's will.

07:15.034 --> 07:16.865
Deal?

07:20.573 --> 07:23.064
[Sam ] Mike,you been doing
some work on the Charger?

07:23.142 --> 07:25.133
There's enough grease
in here to lube a semi.

07:25.211 --> 07:28.874
- You know, these pants are new.
- Yeah, Fi and I have been doing a little work on it.

07:28.948 --> 07:31.508
Exhaust, electrical.

07:31.584 --> 07:33.575
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

07:33.653 --> 07:36.850
- What's wrong with it?
-Just glitchy.

07:36.923 --> 07:38.857
- Glitchy?
- Yeah.

07:38.925 --> 07:41.894
- Well, glitchy's my specialty, Mike.
- Really? Your specialty?

07:41.961 --> 07:44.555
- Yeah.
- I might takeyou up on that. Thanks, Sam.

07:47.333 --> 07:50.166
[Sam ]
Here wego.

07:50.236 --> 07:52.363
I lookedinto these guys
a little bit foryou.

07:52.438 --> 07:55.168
That's Eli Zamar.
He runs the company.

07:55.241 --> 07:57.232
Ari and Ilan are the sons.

07:59.445 --> 08:02.107
Eli's the one that beat up Nate.

08:02.181 --> 08:04.615
The name sounds Israeli,
but Jake said they were Lebanese.

08:04.684 --> 08:07.175
Yeah, the business is registered
there. They got an office here...

08:07.253 --> 08:09.778
- and theygot a hangar out at the airport.
- [ Camera Shutter Clicking]

08:09.856 --> 08:12.518
This guy, Eli, Mike--
I think he's had some training.

08:12.592 --> 08:16.961
Check this out. Every time he comes outside,
he does a perimeter scan. See that?

08:17.029 --> 08:20.226
[ Michael Narrating]
In gathering intel, little things can tellyou a lot.

08:20.299 --> 08:22.961
A topflight alarm system.

08:24.270 --> 08:27.068
Well-placed cameras
without blind spots.

08:27.139 --> 08:29.266
Paying attention to strangers
in the area.

08:29.342 --> 08:30.468
[ Shutter Cl icks ]

08:32.111 --> 08:34.739
- U h-oh. Ti me to go.
- [ Engine Starts ]

08:44.857 --> 08:47.325
[ Michael Narrating ] More aggressive
intelligence gathering is more delicate.

08:47.393 --> 08:50.590
But someone who knows what
to look for can find out a lot.

08:50.663 --> 08:54.565
Hey. [ Chuckles ]
I s this Hangar 1 2?

08:56.369 --> 08:58.894
- What are you looking for?
- Hangar 1 2.

08:58.971 --> 09:03.533
I think. I met this guy at a club, and he--
he told me that he had a private plane...

09:03.609 --> 09:06.476
and that he would take me up in it.

09:06.546 --> 09:11.176
And I-- I get here,
and it's nothing like a regular airport.

09:11.250 --> 09:13.241
No, this is a private airport.

09:15.154 --> 09:19.523
I mean, this is Hangar 1 2,
but, uh, it's notyourfriend's Hangar 1 2.

09:19.592 --> 09:22.083
[ Chuckles ]
God. What a jerk.

09:22.161 --> 09:24.425
- What's the problem?
- It's no problem. Relax.

09:24.497 --> 09:26.658
- You have to leave.
- You guys are working, huh?

09:28.034 --> 09:31.367
You know, before I go,
doyou guys have a-- a bathroom?

09:31.437 --> 09:33.769
I drove all the way
out here from South Beach...

09:33.839 --> 09:37.502
- and it looks like I have to go all the way back--
- I'm sorry. You have to leave.

09:37.577 --> 09:40.171
[ Eli ]
Hey.

09:40.246 --> 09:42.237
[ Foreign Language ]

09:44.717 --> 09:46.776
You're the, uh, boss?

09:46.852 --> 09:49.878
- That's right.
- I-- I was just looking for a bathroom.

09:51.023 --> 09:53.617
No bathroom. Out.

09:53.693 --> 09:55.786
- Okay.
- Now.

09:55.861 --> 09:57.954
God, I just need to pee.

09:58.030 --> 10:00.863
[ Michael Narrating] Ifyou know
what to look for, a bunch oflittle things...

10:00.933 --> 10:02.924
can tellyou everything
you need to know.

